<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4813] NamedPipes may not work in all cases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4813</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The classes provided in current net standard to deal with PipeSecurity are broken, they simply do not work. Hence, in some cases a connection cannot be established. A possible scenario would be between a normal client and an elevated server (think of an UI to control a service process).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ticket references&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/issues/24040&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;issue 24040 NamedPipeServerStream: Provide support for WRITE_DAC&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/issues/34400&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;issue 34400 Have a mechanism for lower privileged user to connect to a privileged user&apos;s pipe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/issues/31190&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;issue 31190 System.IO.Pipes.AccessControl package does not work&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Also interesting in this context is &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/issues/30170&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;issue 30170&lt;/a&gt; which finally got closed and is continued in issue&#160;)31190 (listed above).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
